### Thiruvananthapuram | Posted on Jan 12, 2012 at 12:40pm IST

# NIMS Introduces wireless capsule endoscopy

![indianexpress](http://static.ibnlive.in.com/ibnlive/pix/ibnhome/indian-
express.jpg) Express News Service , The New Indian Express  

Tweet

Share on Tumblr

![Email](http://static.ibnlive.com/pix/ibnhome/prnt_img02.gif)

![Print](http://static.ibnlive.com/pix/ibnhome/email_bottom_img01.gif)

THIRUVANANTHAPURAM: NIMS medicity has introduced wireless capsule endoscopy, a
new diagnostic tool for the detection of small bowel disease non-invasively.

�This technique does not require insertion of endoscope through the mouth.

�Instead of lying down still on an examination table during the exam, patients
can walk after the ingestion of the pill.

People while using wireless endoscopy can walk, sit and even return to normal
work while the capsules are recording images.

�It is also disposable and therefore comfortable to patients.

(For updates you can share with your friends, follow IBNLive on Facebook,
Twitter and Google+)

